description: Municipal Development in South West Serbia, second phase

subproject.description:
The overall objective of the project “Municipal Development in South West Serbia, second phase” (PRO II) is to strengthen local governments in facilitating socio-economic development and improvement of living standards of population in South West Serbia.
The project “Municipal Development in South West Serbia, second phase” will continue to provide support to six municipalities: Novi Pazar, Sjenica, Tutin, Nova Varos, Prijepolje and Priboj, initiate activities in municipality of Raska and provide support to intermunicipal activities through establishment of regional development agencies (in line with feasibility reports). 
The specific purpose of the project is to achieve two interdependent goals: to enhance good local governance in all municipalities in South West Serbia at the same time to improve overall socio-economic situation through implementation of strategic priorities on the municipal and inter-municipal (regional) level financed by municipalities and other direct (foreign and domestic) investments.
